title: Hull boy dies after choking on his food during lunch break
text: Share this article Share Yorkshire Ambulance Service confirmed they attended the school yesterday in an attempt to save the boy's life. A spokeswoman said: 'Following the tragic outcome, our thoughts remain with the family at this difficult time.' Headmaster Gareth May said the 'whole school community is deeply saddened' by the tragic death Council staff are offering support to teachers and pupils at the school following the boy's death. A spokesman for East Riding Council said: 'Very sadly, we have been informed that a foundation stage pupil at Anlaby Primary School has died. 'The council is offering close support to the school and to the child's family.' Yorkshire Ambulance Service confirmed they attended the school yesterday in an attempt to save the boy's life. A spokeswoman said: 'Following the tragic outcome, our thoughts remain with the family at this difficult time.' An inquest into the boy's death is expected to take place at Hull Coroner's Court.
